00:16:39,080 --> 00:16:41,150
Please ignore him.

235
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:43,515
This is my dad Richard,
"Call me Dickie."

236
00:16:43,600 --> 00:16:44,999
Are you following this?

237
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:47,719
- Dad, this is Kim.
- Call me Dickie.

238
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:50,872
Thank you for stepping in.
Just do whatever Georgie does.

239
00:16:50,960 --> 00:16:52,598
Except that thing with her chin.

240
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:55,029
- We liked that, didn't we?
- That was a one-off.

241
00:16:55,120 --> 00:16:57,759
- Speaking of one-offs...
- Hey!

242
00:16:57,840 --> 00:16:59,319
Hello.

243
00:16:59,400 --> 00:17:01,834
This is my wife Caroline.

244
00:17:03,760 --> 00:17:06,638
Who apparently has a throat infection.

245
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,392
- Help us with the bags?
- Ah, yes.

246
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:13,077
- Ahem.
- Give her a chance.

247
00:17:13,160 --> 00:17:15,594
I didn't say anything.

248
00:17:22,040 --> 00:17:25,749
(Georgie) And lovingly topped off
with gravy, a la me.

249
00:17:29,520 --> 00:17:31,317
Back office.

250
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:35,232
Wouldn't want to steal your thunder
with the sprouts.

251
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:39,037
Oh, brilliant. Look at that!

252
00:17:45,360 --> 00:17:47,555
(all exclaim)

253
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:56,349
Ibble dibble number one, with 12 ibble
dibbles calls ibble dibble number...

254
00:18:01,280 --> 00:18:03,589
There. Right there.

255
00:18:04,120 --> 00:18:08,671
Mmm! I want to be a profiterole.

256
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:10,637
So these guys fly in on a private jet

257
00:18:10,720 --> 00:18:14,076
and their idea of fun is rubbing
a burnt cork on each other's faces?

258
00:18:14,160 --> 00:18:15,718
That's insane.

259
00:18:15,800 --> 00:18:19,509
Sanity's overrated.
Tried it once, didn't get it.

260
00:18:22,200 --> 00:18:23,792
Join in. We don't bite.

261
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:27,395
Well, my mum bites a bit. The rest of us
just nibble ibble dibble...

262
00:18:27,480 --> 00:18:28,913
Talking crap.

263
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:31,434
- You! It's time.
- No, there's absolutely no way.

264
00:18:31,520 --> 00:18:33,750
- Yes! Yes!
- I don't want to!

265
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:38,438
Georgie! Georgie! Georgie! Georgie!

266
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:40,551
OK, OK.

267
00:18:40,640 --> 00:18:42,039
Hark! The Herald.

268
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:46,309
Ooh.

269
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:50,598
(makes farting sounds to tune of
"Hark! The Herald Angels Sing")

270
00:18:55,440 --> 00:18:57,874
(mimics beatbox)

271
00:18:57,960 --> 00:19:00,599
- Go, go, go.
- (Chloe) Oh, Nigel.

272
00:19:00,680 --> 00:19:01,999
(Dickie) Yeah, yeah, yeah.

273
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:08,397
See now, this is my idea of fun.
You should join in.

274
00:19:08,520 --> 00:19:11,318
(all) # Hark! The herald angels sing

275
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:15,234
Unfortunately I'm only grade one
at... whatever that is.

276
00:19:17,400 --> 00:19:19,038
Yeah!

277
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:22,669
- You eating alright?
- Five a day. How's it going?

278
00:19:22,760 --> 00:19:25,320
- It's fine.
- What are the people like?

279
00:19:25,400 --> 00:19:27,311
- (excited shrieking)
- They're...

280
00:19:27,400 --> 00:19:29,197
Who wants more champagne?

281
00:19:29,280 --> 00:19:30,872
..fine.

282
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:34,191
If it doesn't work out, I can
always nick one of their paintings.

283
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:36,236
- (beeping)
- What's that noise?

284
00:19:36,320 --> 00:19:38,629
Oh, nothing, er...

285
00:19:38,720 --> 00:19:42,474
No, it's next door.
There's a truck reversing,

286
00:19:42,560 --> 00:19:44,118
I think.

287
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:47,990
Listen, Kimmy,

288
00:19:48,080 --> 00:19:49,593
I really miss you, you know?

289
00:19:49,680 --> 00:19:52,911
I know, Dad. Me too.

290
00:19:59,800 --> 00:20:02,792
(Kim) Georgie? Georgie?

291
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:05,353
It's seven.

292
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:07,396
(Georgie groans)

293
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:10,194
Rule two?

294
00:20:17,400 --> 00:20:19,960
- Is this caviar?
- Sure looks like it.

295
00:20:20,040 --> 00:20:24,830
Well, dig in, everyone,
and enjoy your $300 omelettes.

296
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:31,680
Jesus, Kim. You have to wake me.
I don't need you making me look bad.

297
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:34,115
- No kidding.
- (shrieks)

298
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:36,760
So what am I supposed
to do all day, then?

299
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:42,039
I don't know. I'm sure
you'll find something. Look around.

300
00:21:10,040 --> 00:21:11,268
Oh, shit.

301
00:21:12,320 --> 00:21:14,311
Wait! Stop!

302
00:21:31,360 --> 00:21:33,874
- Georgie, this cake is supreme.
- Thank you, Jonny.

303
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,871
(Nigel) Hm-hmm! Sure is.

304
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:38,878
- This place is so magical.
- It is when you're here.

305
00:21:38,960 --> 00:21:41,997
Enjoy it. You won't ski this much
when you're starting a family.

306
00:21:42,080 --> 00:21:45,197
- Do I get a say in any of this?
- No, snoogles, you don't.

307
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:48,750
I'm not sure I'm ready for any of this.
Do I look like a grandfather?

308
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:51,115
- Don't answer that!
- (Chloe laughs)

309
00:21:52,480 --> 00:21:54,914
Thank you. Ooh.

310
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,831
(shrieks)

311
00:21:57,920 --> 00:21:59,399
That's hot!

312
00:22:14,520 --> 00:22:19,389
# Angels watching over me
with smiles upon their face

313
00:22:19,480 --> 00:22:24,429
# Cos I have made it through this far
in an unforgiving place

314
00:22:24,520 --> 00:22:29,036
# It feels sometimes this hill's
too steep for a girl like me to climb

315
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:32,634
# But I must knock those thoughts
right down

316
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:34,676
# I'll do it in my own time

317
00:22:34,760 --> 00:22:36,478
# I don 't care

318
00:22:36,560 --> 00:22:38,915
# I'm halfway there

319
00:22:40,000 --> 00:22:43,276
# On a road that leads me
straight to who knows where

320
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:44,555
(yells)

321
00:22:49,120 --> 00:22:51,588
You crazy freak!
Watch where you're going!

322
00:22:51,680 --> 00:22:53,398
I'm so sorry. Sorry.

323
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:56,313
Stay safe, Betty Boop.
Hang outside on the ripside!

324
00:22:56,400 --> 00:23:00,916
- Yeah, and in English?
- Hang outside on the ripside.

325
00:23:03,240 --> 00:23:04,389
Ciao!

326
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:06,670
# I tell you what

327
00:23:06,760 --> 00:23:09,433
# What I have found

328
00:23:09,520 --> 00:23:12,080
# That I'm no fool

329
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:14,720
# I'm just upside down

330
00:23:14,840 --> 00:23:16,910
# Ain't got no cares

331
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:19,958
# I ain't got no rules

332
00:23:20,040 --> 00:23:22,429
# I think I like

333
00:23:22,520 --> 00:23:25,159
# Living upside down

334
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:29,073
# You gotta slow it down

335
00:23:29,160 --> 00:23:31,549
- (yells)
- # But then you pick it up

336
00:23:32,480 --> 00:23:35,950
# Come on and try a little topsy-turvy
back-to-front the right way round

337
00:23:38,840 --> 00:23:41,354
You blow at boarding.
But you sure are styley.

338
00:23:41,440 --> 00:23:43,908
I'll take it you're not
into pink all-in-ones?

339
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:45,149
(laughs)

340
00:23:48,640 --> 00:23:53,953
- Mikki. Single guy from Finland.
- Kim. Not interested from England.

341
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:57,913
- You know the skateboarding?
- A bit.

342
00:23:58,040 --> 00:24:00,395
Same, same, but different.
You want some help?

343
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:05,074
- Yeah.
- OK, come on, get up.

344
00:24:07,800 --> 00:24:12,271
OK, in skateboarding, weight back.
In snowboarding, weight centred.

345
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:15,790
OK. Right.

346
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:17,518
- Knees.
- OK.

347
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:22,953
Turn with your shoulders,
not the knees.

348
00:24:23,920 --> 00:24:25,876
You're a natural.

349
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,718
It's like skateboarding, huh?

350
00:24:27,840 --> 00:24:29,114
(Kim) Whoo-hoo!

351
00:24:29,200 --> 00:24:30,553
(laughs)

352
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:34,679
- That was pretty cool.
- That was nothing, Betty.

353
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:36,512
Let's get high.

354
00:24:36,600 --> 00:24:38,079
Up.

355
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:41,317
Oh. No, I can't. I'm on the budget tour.

356
00:24:41,400 --> 00:24:43,914
Betty... Follow me.

357
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:57,996
Hey, look. That's the biggest
snowboarding competition in Tyrol.

358
00:24:58,080 --> 00:25:01,755
Every year I enter,
every year I face-plant.

359
00:25:01,840 --> 00:25:03,910
But this year I rock it!

360
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:06,150
Hey, we'll enter together.

361
00:25:06,280 --> 00:25:08,475
Why? Because I'm such a pro boarder?

362
00:25:08,560 --> 00:25:10,676
Three months, maybe.

363
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:13,399
Maybe, maybe not.

364
00:25:13,480 --> 00:25:17,234
Come on. $25,000. It's easy for you.
You're a skateboarder.

365
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:20,198
I pulled a 360 my first day on a board.

366
00:25:20,320 --> 00:25:23,392
- (Kim) And broke your neck, right?
- (Mikki) No. My leg.

367
00:25:24,800 --> 00:25:27,394
Just so you know,
I've given Jonny your mother's ring.

368
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:31,155
That's a coincidence. I've given him
one of her dresses. He'll look lovely.

369
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:33,879
It is not funny.
The marquee is pencilled for June.

370
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:36,713
It was quite funny.

371
00:25:36,800 --> 00:25:39,997
Didn't you get the message?
You're joining us. Dress up.

372
00:25:40,840 --> 00:25:42,478
I... did.

373
00:25:42,560 --> 00:25:44,437
Don't worry. She made me change too.

374
00:25:44,520 --> 00:25:48,752
Drainpipe jeans and winkle-pickers
aren't very this season apparently.

375
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:52,671
(Chloe) You were never a style guru.

376
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:54,478
(Jonny) I was.

377
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:58,870
Lippy.

378
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,399
Liner.

379
00:26:00,480 --> 00:26:01,993
Lashes.

380
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,991
Accessories.

381
00:26:04,080 --> 00:26:05,433
I want those back.

382
00:26:05,520 --> 00:26:08,557
And... hair gum. Use sparingly.

383
00:26:08,640 --> 00:26:10,358
Hair gum?

384
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:20,752
And like that, she became a swan.

385
00:26:20,840 --> 00:26:22,751
So I used to be an ugly duckling, then?

386
00:26:22,840 --> 00:26:25,400
Someone needs to learn
how to take a compliment.

387
00:26:26,960 --> 00:26:30,396
- Ah, it all makes sense now.
- Yeah. I'm just back office.

388
00:26:35,960 --> 00:26:38,872
- It's a shoelace.
- Er, it's bow tie.

389
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:42,356
No, it's a shoelace knot. Come here.

390
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:50,436
Didn't think you'd be the kind of girl
who knew how to tie a bow tie.

391
00:26:50,520 --> 00:26:53,432
And here's me thinking
you were the kind of boy who would.

392
00:26:58,760 --> 00:27:01,035
Big night for you, then?

393
00:27:08,360 --> 00:27:10,590
There.

394
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:12,671
Licensed to kill.

395
00:27:14,280 --> 00:27:16,919
- Or be killed.
- (laughs)

396
00:27:26,160 --> 00:27:28,515
(Jonny) Right, who needs a drink?

397
00:27:30,200 --> 00:27:34,910
- Oh, Georgie. What are these?
- Mini-burgers. Don't blame me.

398
00:27:35,040 --> 00:27:37,713
They are sensational.

399
00:27:37,800 --> 00:27:40,394
- Trying to get me drunk?
- Just helping you on your way.

400
00:27:40,480 --> 00:27:42,357
Greasing your nuts, as it were.

401
00:27:42,440 --> 00:27:45,193
- Rule three?
- Oh, shut up.

402
00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:48,151
What are you grinning at?

403
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:51,397
Nothing. Just think
I'm starting to get the hang of this.

404
00:27:51,480 --> 00:27:55,314
The cake's on the oven. The beef
is nearly done. And the mousse has set.

405
00:27:55,400 --> 00:27:57,231
Oh, thank you.

406
00:27:59,440 --> 00:28:01,396
Thank you.

407
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:04,119
- Wow. Did you hear what...
- Yeah, don't get used to it.

408
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:06,151
Get a fresh one of these.

409
00:28:06,240 --> 00:28:08,708
Such responsibility.
Do I get a performance star?

410
00:28:08,800 --> 00:28:10,791
- What?
- Doesn't matter.

411
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:22,476
Chloe, you look wonderful.

412
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:33,111
Oh, look. Looks like the new girl's
putting on pre-dinner entertainment.

413
00:28:33,200 --> 00:28:35,634
Oh, dear, stand back.

414
00:28:35,720 --> 00:28:36,869
Kim, wait. Kim...

415
00:28:40,960 --> 00:28:43,315
(Caroline) What a waste. That's vintage.

416
00:28:49,240 --> 00:28:52,516
Doctor's orders. The good news is,
you've already got the headache,

417
00:28:52,600 --> 00:28:54,318
so you can drink as much as you like.

418
00:28:54,400 --> 00:28:56,789
- I should go and help Georgie.
- I wouldn't worry.

419
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:59,838
- I think Nigel has her covered.
- Thanks.

420
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:09,151
- Hit the spot.
- Yeah, it should. '62 Dom.

421
00:29:09,240 --> 00:29:12,437
- Dom?
- It's 500 quid a bottle.

422
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:16,638
500? Think I'll just take the cash
next time.

423
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:21,228
Why am I here?
I'm stuck in a parallel reality

424
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:24,039
where people drink my monthly salary
every ten minutes.

425
00:29:24,120 --> 00:29:28,477
You're right. We're aliens.
My mother has a tail. Did you see it?

426
00:29:28,560 --> 00:29:30,755
Your mum is the scariest woman
I've ever met.

427
00:29:30,840 --> 00:29:34,071
You want to know how she met
my dad? Air stewardess. Concorde.

428
00:29:34,160 --> 00:29:36,833
Your dad was an air stewardess?

429
00:29:38,400 --> 00:29:39,628
She's not that scary.

430
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:44,197
Well, look, I should be getting back.

431
00:29:44,280 --> 00:29:48,592
Yeah, of course. Thanks for the Dom.

432
00:29:50,840 --> 00:29:52,558
Yeah.

433
00:30:04,920 --> 00:30:06,717
(Jonny) Can we talk about this later?

434
00:30:06,800 --> 00:30:09,872
(Caroline)
She won't wait forever, Jonny.

435
00:30:09,960 --> 00:30:12,554
(sighs) I feel so sorry for her.

436
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:15,433
See?

437
00:30:18,120 --> 00:30:19,872
- Thank you.
- Everything alright?

438
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:23,549
Yeah, everything's fine.
We'll be back out in February.

439
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:26,871
See if you can figure out the whole
champagne-bottle thing by then.

440
00:30:26,960 --> 00:30:30,509
- Yep, I will practise daily.
- Knock yourself out.

441
00:30:31,720 --> 00:30:34,678
Trying to shake your hand,
punch you in the stomach. Not cool.

442
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:37,115
So, I'll put the photos on Facebook.

443
00:30:38,080 --> 00:30:40,230
Well,... poke me.

444
00:30:41,840 --> 00:30:44,149
Right. OK, girls.

445
00:30:44,240 --> 00:30:47,596
This is for all your hard work.
Thank you so much.

446
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:50,558
And, Kim, you know you get
a lift pass too, don't you?

447
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:55,031
Just charge it to the chalet.
Unless you'd prefer the cash.

448
00:30:55,120 --> 00:30:57,270
- Lift pass would be great.
- OK.

449
00:30:57,360 --> 00:31:00,158
- Alright, let's go.
- It's a private plane. It can wait.

450
00:31:00,280 --> 00:31:02,874
- It will. I won't.
- Desperate to get back to work.

451
00:31:02,960 --> 00:31:05,679
OK, maybe I'll quit,
and next time we can hitchhike here.

452
00:31:05,760 --> 00:31:08,558
A father-son adventure.
I like the sound of that. Bye.

453
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:16,714
- "Poke me"?
- Piss off.

454
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:18,319
Slut.

455
00:31:19,720 --> 00:31:22,234
- 200-euro tip for one week?
- (microwave pings)

456
00:31:22,320 --> 00:31:24,072
Are you sure you're just cooking?

457
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:27,869
I'll put it in the bank when I can.
You OK?

458
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:30,392
- Yeah. Solid.
- Huh?

459
00:31:30,480 --> 00:31:32,311
I mean sound, yeah.

460
00:31:32,400 --> 00:31:35,870
- Don't let them work you too hard.
- I won't.

461
00:31:47,360 --> 00:31:50,079
(Kim) Right, Finland, let's do this.
Where do we start?

462
00:31:50,160 --> 00:31:55,075
Well, in slopestyle, you are scored
on your tricks on the rails,

463
00:31:55,160 --> 00:31:56,798
and the jump you pull at the end.

464
00:31:56,880 --> 00:32:00,555
- You smell me?
- Yes, I smell you. Unfortunately.

465
00:32:02,080 --> 00:32:05,868
Think about the run. Only the run.
Be the board.

466
00:32:09,080 --> 00:32:11,230
Let's get tricky with Mikki!

467
00:32:11,320 --> 00:32:12,958
(yells)

468
00:32:15,320 --> 00:32:16,389
(whoops)

469
00:32:17,520 --> 00:32:19,556
Right, come on, Kim.

470
00:32:24,200 --> 00:32:25,713
(yells)

471
00:32:34,240 --> 00:32:35,719
(whoops)

472
00:32:38,400 --> 00:32:40,356
Yes! (whoops)

473
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:47,434
- Hey.
- Hey.

474
00:32:47,520 --> 00:32:51,559
You do realise you're riding a beginner
board from, like, the 16th century?

475
00:32:51,640 --> 00:32:55,030
I thought the 16th century
was the golden age of snowboarding.

476
00:32:55,120 --> 00:32:57,873
Go to the rental shop
and pick yourself up a park board.

477
00:32:57,960 --> 00:33:00,030
You'll have more fun on that, trust me.

478
